This paper deals with mechanism design in the context of one-sided matching, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the use of convex combinations, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.AI) and optimization (cs.DS). The paper also presents numerical results, which suggests the use of computational methods (cs.LG) and simulation (cs.MA).
